11-12.contemplation:
Contemplate the resurrected Lord Jesus:

1. How He appeared to the disciples on the road to Emmaus;

2. How they did not recognize Him until the breaking of bread;

3. How they knew Him and He disappeared from their sight.

11-13.contemplation:
Contemplate the resurrected Lord Jesus:

1. How He appeared to Mary Magdalene, who loved Him more than herself;

2. How Mary at first did not recognize Him, and how she later knew Him when He called her by name;

3. How Mary, in her joy, wanted to embrace Him, but He would not allow her, saying: Touch Me not, for I am not yet ascended to My Father (John 20:17).

11-14.contemplation:
Contemplate the resurrected Lord Jesus:

1. How He appeared to the disciples in the upper room;

2. How He showed them His hands and His side;

3. How He said to them: Peace be unto you.
